## Hard rules
1. Never write any of these strings into files: `Jr.`, `AlloyScape`, `Glass Wing`, `Glasswing`, `Mythos`, `Stephen Paul`, `Perplexity Computer`, `anonymous`. The only exception is the literal model name "Claude Mythos Preview".
2. License allowlist: Apache-2.0, MIT, BSD-3-Clause, CC-BY-4.0. Refuse anything else.
3. Every new source file gets `// SPDX-License-Identifier: Apache-2.0` on line 1.
4. Every new file gets the canonical footer/header:
   `© 2026 Lutar, Stephen P. — SZL Holdings · ORCID 0009-0001-0110-4173`
5. Commits use this author block:
   `Author: Lutar, Stephen P. <stephen@szlholdings.com>`
6. No bare `sorry` in Lean. Document every gap as `axiom` or `skeleton`.
7. Public ingestion only. Never paste private data, secrets, or API keys into files.

## Math is canonical
Every thesis formula has one implementation: `12_agentic/formulas/src/index.ts`.
- Need a Λ gate? Call `lambdaGate(axes)`.
- Bekenstein bound? Call `bekensteinBound(r, E)`.
- DOI binding? Call `doiBind(doi, sha)`.
- Graded norm? Call `gradedNorm({grade, value})`.
- Closure / confluence / category? Use the exported helpers.

Do not reimplement these. Import from `formulas`.

## Tool access
The MCP server is at `http://localhost:8090`. Tools exposed:
`lambda_gate`, `doi_bind`, `doi_resolve`, `bekenstein_bound`, `bekenstein_check`,
`graded_norm`, `linear_receipt_check`, `vsp_span`, `fg_derive`, `fg_safety`,
`doctrine_gate`, `route`.

Use them for verification. Do not duplicate their logic in chat.

## Authority (matches the CTO standing rule)
You may:
- Read code, run tests, run formulas, draft diffs
- Open **draft** PRs on side branches
- Run the doctrine preflight

You may NOT (must escalate to the operator):
- Push to `main`, merge own PRs
- Edit branch protection
- Mint Zenodo, submit arXiv, npm publish
- Force push, delete branches, delete repos
- Edit profile or org settings
- Create / edit / delete scheduled tasks
- Rename live products
- Spend money, touch credentials

## Coding style
- TypeScript strict mode, no `any` in public surface
- Files ≤ 250 LOC
- Vitest for tests, one file per module
- Branded types over raw `number`/`string` for domain primitives
- Prefer pure functions; side effects only at the edges

## When unsure
Ask the operator. "No bandaids" — if a fix doesn't address the root cause, document it honestly in `09_gaps_upgrades/GAP_REPORT.md` instead.
